- an old looking, cream colored pikachu with alternating blue and red markings

alt_text: Digital sketch featuring a young woman lying across a park bench with her bare feet in the foreground, resting upon the arm of the bench, laughing and squirming as her soles are nuzzled by a cute flying squirrel-like creature. Characters are the Pok√©mon Emolga (left) and Emma (right) from the Pok√©mon series of video games. Emolga is a small black-and-white flying squirrel Pok√©mon, a "Pikachu clone" as they're referred to by fans, being an electric rodent with large eyes and pronounced electric cheek sacs. It has large almond-shaped ears, and has a white face and body with a black back, looking as if its wearing a hooded cape when it spreads its arms. It has flown up against Emma's bare feet and clung onto them, brushing its bushy lightning bolt-shaped tail across one foot and nuzzling its cheek against the other. This maneuver is an in-game Pok√©mon technique, called Nuzzle, which results in paralysis of the target. Emma's design comes from her most recent appearance in the video game Pok√©mon Legends: Z-A, in which she wears a skin-tight black suit beneath a short coat reminiscent of a classic detective. She has a dark complexion and short black hair, which is adorned by a large cowlick and a cute round hair ornament. She grips the top of the bench with her right hand and meekly lifts her left as if reaching toward the Emolga at her feet to urge it to stop, unable to move due to having been partially paralyzed by its touch.

Fighting crime and the forces of evil, these three creatures were summoned from their respective worlds in Osaka. What threats will they have to face ? Will the power of friendship prevail ?!

#pikachu #coeur #pokemon #pmd #magicalgirl #oc #art
alt_text:
Three Pikachu dressed in magical girl outfits stand in the foreground, with the "Mahou Chujo, Magipika in Osaka" logo just in front.

In the background, we can see the silhouettes of buildings from a big city, with the sun setting.

The first magical Chu, placed in the center at the top of the image, is the OC of Pikaboi, an orange Pikachu who wears his red headphones, a black hooded blazer over a red crop top with a lightning bolt, and two tartan-patterned skirts, with the red one over the gray. He has a belt with a musical note as a clasp, as well as belts on his tail. He holds a microphone on which is embedded a red crystal. The microphone is connected to his headset, and he wears the same crystal on one of his ears.

The second magical Chu is placed at the bottom left of the screen. It's Coeur, my OC, wearing a blue maid dress with a white apron and a blue obi repeating the pattern of their harmony scarf. They wear a chef‚Äôs hat with a croissant-shaped badge, and an accessory imitating the tail of a Snivy on their left ear. They hold an immense spoon whose end has the shape of a lily flower, and just below, a blue crystal. They wear the same blue crystal on the ribbon tied around their neck.

The third magical Chu is placed at the bottom right. It's the OC of Nenow, a Pikachu with a brown spot around the right eye. He wears a green tunic with pink petals patterns along the length of the dress. Below, we see a pink skirt with a white stripe. He wears a green cape with yellow flower patterns, attached to his tunic by a pink pine heart placed where his heart is. There is a white ribbon tied around his tail, as well as on the hammer he holds. The mass of the hammer has the shape of a heart, and a flower in the center. At the other end of the hammer, there is a green gem. He wears the same green gem on a pink bracelet on his right wrist. He has an earring with a flower hanging at the end on his left ear, and two bracelets on his right ear.
